				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Double bind points is MUCH more powerful and less prone to disaster than the port/evac sets.  A porter CAN bind in zone, but since that sets his reincarnation point to there, there is inherant risk of death loops.  With a double bind you can set your reincarnation point safely at the bank, and your secondary bind in any incredibly dangerous spot without serious risk.  It would be very nice, but the wizards and druids would have good reason to scream bloody murder at it.  Frankly, the game has given us a very valid set of ports, the Adventurer Camps.  Certainly not as useful as the Wizard and Druid range, but certainly something.
